{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Frank. I can get you out.

946
01:23:18,228 --> 01:23:19,717
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Don't do it!

947
01:23:19,897 --> 01:23:22,296
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-No, Frank, no!
-Frank, no!

948
01:23:23,968 --> 01:23:25,832
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Frank!

949
01:24:09,346 --> 01:24:11,245
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What have you got there?

950
01:24:12,149 --> 01:24:14,548
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}A Gutenberg Bible.

951
01:24:14,752 --> 01:24:17,049
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It was in the rare books room.

952
01:24:18,355 --> 01:24:20,049
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You think God's gonna save you?

953
01:24:20,824 --> 01:24:23,587
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No. I don't believe in God.

954
01:24:24,261 --> 01:24:26,922
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You're holding onto that Bible
pretty tight.

955
01:24:27,097 --> 01:24:29,087
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm protecting it.

956
01:24:32,603 --> 01:24:36,094
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}This Bible is the first book ever printed.

957
01:24:36,940 --> 01:24:41,899
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It represents the dawn
of the age of reason.

958
01:24:42,279 --> 01:24:46,305
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}As far as I'm concerned, the written word
is mankind's greatest achievement.

959
01:24:46,650 --> 01:24:48,207
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You can laugh.

960
01:24:49,186 --> 01:24:52,313
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But if Western civilization is finished...

961
01:24:52,956 --> 01:24:56,948
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}...I'm gonna save
at least one little piece of it.

962
01:25:33,696 --> 01:25:35,822
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We heard somebody was left behind.

963
01:25:36,766 --> 01:25:40,462
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-We brought an ambulance.
-Thank God.

964
01:25:42,939 --> 01:25:45,668
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Thank you so much for coming.

965
01:26:06,596 --> 01:26:08,119
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hey.

966
01:26:09,031 --> 01:26:11,225
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hey, are you all right?

967
01:26:12,468 --> 01:26:14,662
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You look like you have a fever
or something.

968
01:26:14,837 --> 01:26:17,964
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm fine. I just can't sleep.

969
01:26:20,877 --> 01:26:26,405
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}My mind keeps going over
all those worthless decathlon facts.

970
01:26:28,017 --> 01:26:30,314
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-It's pretty stupid, huh?
-No, it's all right.

971
01:26:30,486 --> 01:26:33,977
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I guess you just haven't had time
to adjust yet.

972
01:26:35,758 --> 01:26:38,351
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}How am I supposed to adjust, Sam?

973
01:26:38,928 --> 01:26:42,863
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Everything I've ever cared about,
everything I've worked for...

974
01:26:43,399 --> 01:26:47,027
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}...has all been preparation
for a future that no longer exists.

975
01:26:50,506 --> 01:26:54,532
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I know you always thought I took
the competition too seriously.

976
01:26:55,845 --> 01:26:57,675
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You were right.

977
01:26:58,281 --> 01:27:01,249
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-lt was all for nothing.
-No, no. I--

978
01:27:02,184 --> 01:27:06,449
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No, I just-- I just said that
to avoid admitting the truth.

979
01:27:07,856 --> 01:27:09,516
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Truth about what?

980
01:27:13,562 --> 01:27:16,928
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}About why I joined the team.

981
01:27:22,070 --> 01:27:24,230
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I joined it because of you.

982
01:27:37,319 --> 01:27:38,785
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hey.

983
01:28:04,579 --> 01:28:06,307
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I know.

984
01:28:06,648 --> 01:28:07,875
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I know.

985
01:28:08,049 --> 01:28:10,141
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-Mr. President.
-All right.

986
01:28:10,852 --> 01:28:13,251
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm sorry, sir, we can't wait any longer.

987
01:28:13,822 --> 01:28:15,812
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We're the last ones.

988
01:28:16,725 --> 01:28:18,282
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}All right.

989
01:28:33,308 --> 01:28:35,070
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mexicali Control, this is Delta 26.

990
01:28:36,678 --> 01:28:38,645
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We've got an urgent message
for high command.

991
01:28:38,813 --> 01:28:41,007
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Request priority for landing zone one.

992
01:28:41,182 --> 01:28:45,140
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Roger that, Delta 26.
Transport will be waiting.

993
01:28:50,225 --> 01:28:51,589
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-Sir.
-Thank you, corporal.

994
01:28:51,760 --> 01:28:53,954
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-Sorry for the delay, sir.
-Carry on.

995
01:29:06,740 --> 01:29:08,604
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Madam Secretary.

996
01:29:18,152 --> 01:29:19,778
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Raymond.

997
01:29:20,721 --> 01:29:23,211
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The president's motorcade
got caught in the storm.

998
01:29:28,295 --> 01:29:29,886
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They didn't make it.

999
01:29:36,270 --> 01:29:38,794
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And she wouldn't wake up
this morning. I--

1000
01:29:38,972 --> 01:29:41,405
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She only had a fever.
I don't understand.

1001
01:29:41,575 --> 01:29:43,735
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She's awfully pale.

1002
01:29:43,977 --> 01:29:46,444
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}None of us has had anything
real to eat in days.

1003
01:29:46,613 --> 01:29:49,604
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-It's hypothermia.
-But how can it be hypothermia?

1004
01:29:49,783 --> 01:29:51,841
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-We've all been in--
-Maybe it's the flu.

1005
01:29:52,019 --> 01:29:54,316
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No, no, it's not the flu.

1006
01:29:55,556 --> 01:29:56,749
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And how do you know?

1007
01:29:57,257 --> 01:30:00,851
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Books can be good for things other
than burning. What are her symptoms?

1008
01:30:01,028 --> 01:30:04,758
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I told you that she has a fever and her--
She's got a really cold sweat.

1009
01:30:04,932 --> 01:30:06,694
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}How's her pulse?

1010
01:30:07,134 --> 01:30:09,533
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-It's really fast.
-Does she have any injuries?

1011
01:30:09,703 --> 01:30:12,227
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Like a cut that might have
gotten infected?

1012
01:30:12,406 --> 01:30:15,897
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She was complaining about a cut
on her leg a few days ago.

1013
01:30:16,443 --> 01:30:19,275
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I didn't think anything of it.

1014
01:30:23,751 --> 01:30:25,445
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, my gosh.

1015
01:30:26,687 --> 01:30:29,814
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}That's blood poisoning. Septicemia.

1016
01:30:29,990 --> 01:30:32,116
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She could go into septic shock.

1017
01:30:32,292 --> 01:30:34,384
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I've seen that before.
That can get bad.

1018
01:30:34,561 --> 01:30:36,585
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She needs a massive dose
of penicillin...

1019
01:30:36,764 --> 01:30:40,358
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}...or a broad-spectrum
antibiotic immediately, or....

1020
01:30:46,139 --> 01:30:47,730
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Or what?

1021
01:31:07,560 --> 01:31:09,857
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I've never seen anything like it.

1022
01:31:10,062 --> 01:31:13,690
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}There's no point of reference.
All I can see is cloud cover.

1023
01:31:13,866 --> 01:31:15,355
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What are you doing?

1024
01:31:15,535 --> 01:31:17,866
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Taking infrared image of thermal currents.

1025
01:31:18,037 --> 01:31:22,769
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Send to Houston, Korolev,
your weather service.

1026
01:31:22,942 --> 01:31:24,533
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'll help you.

1027
01:31:25,611 --> 01:31:28,044
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Tom? Tom, wake up.

1028
01:31:28,214 --> 01:31:32,582
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I just received some satellite images from
the space station. You better take a look.

1029
01:31:44,130 --> 01:31:45,653
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}How big is this thing?

1030
01:31:45,832 --> 01:31:47,856
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The vortex is 50 miles in diameter.

1031
01:31:48,034 --> 01:31:51,696
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And growing. The two cells
over Europe and Asia are even bigger.

1032
01:31:51,871 --> 01:31:53,167
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Good God.

1033
01:31:53,339 --> 01:31:56,273
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}This one's gonna hit New York
inside an hour.

1034
01:32:12,758 --> 01:32:14,247
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Jason!

1035
01:32:14,427 --> 01:32:16,053
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Are you all right?

1036
01:32:16,529 --> 01:32:18,325
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Jason!

1037
01:32:34,280 --> 01:32:37,578
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-What are you doing?
-There's gotta be medicine on that ship.

1038
01:32:38,117 --> 01:32:41,279
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I thought you said it was too dangerous
to go outside.

1039
01:32:41,453 --> 01:32:42,783
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I know I did.

1040
01:32:49,094 --> 01:32:51,493
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Where did you find those chairs?

1041
01:32:52,831 --> 01:32:54,195
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Why?

1042
01:32:55,066 --> 01:32:56,589
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm going with you.

1043
01:32:58,103 --> 01:32:59,569
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Me too.

1044
01:34:03,068 --> 01:34:04,967
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Come on, damn it!

1045
01:34:53,651 --> 01:34:56,084
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-It's all in Russian. I--
-I know.

1046
01:34:56,487 --> 01:34:59,717
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-Hey, hey, hey, guys. I found it.
-What? How do you know?

1047
01:35:00,224 --> 01:35:02,521
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Because it says "penicillin"
on the bottle.

1048
01:35:07,898 --> 01:35:09,592
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hey, wait. This is the mess hall.

1049
01:35:09,767 --> 01:35:12,132
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-We should find some food.
-We don't have time.

1050
01:35:12,302 --> 01:35:16,294
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Listen, none of us are gonna survive much
longer without food. Including Laura.

1051
01:35:17,574 --> 01:35:18,870
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Okay.

1052
01:35:23,747 --> 01:35:26,340
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-Sam, over here.
-What?

1053
01:35:26,884 --> 01:35:28,578
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Bingo.

1054
01:35:39,630 --> 01:35:41,256
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Brian?

1055
01:35:41,965 --> 01:35:44,660
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-I'm okay.
-What happened?

1056
01:35:45,669 --> 01:35:47,727
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}All I did was open up the cupboard.

1057
01:35:48,605 --> 01:35:51,072
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-Well, we can use it.
-Put food in it.

1058
01:36:03,987 --> 01:36:05,954
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Pull him in, Brian!

1059
01:36:08,525 --> 01:36:11,857
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-You all right?
-Oh, my God, there's more.

1060
01:36:14,064 --> 01:36:15,860
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}My leg.

1061
01:36:19,703 --> 01:36:21,636
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Here, use this.

1062
01:36:29,278 --> 01:36:31,245
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It should be over New York by now.

1063
01:36:32,115 --> 01:36:36,608
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Satellite readings are showing a temperature
drop of 1 0 degrees per second.

1064
01:36:52,201 --> 01:36:53,599
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You guys...

1065
01:36:53,770 --> 01:36:55,828
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}...I think we're in the eye of it.

1066
01:36:56,939 --> 01:36:58,803
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We gotta get back right now.

1067
01:37:00,209 --> 01:37:04,338
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Look, I'm gonna go outside, and I'm gonna
lure the wolves out of the room.

1068
01:37:04,514 --> 01:37:06,845
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}When they leave, you lock the door.

1069
01:37:07,416 --> 01:37:08,643
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Good luck.

1070
01:38:14,617 --> 01:38:17,210
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}-Brian, hurry.
-I need something.

1071
01:38:17,953 --> 01:38:19,886
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Come on, hurry!

1072
01:38:29,664 --> 01:38:31,790
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Brian! Brian, open the door!

1073
01:38:36,605 --> 01:38:38,469
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We have to get out of here now.

1074
01:38:38,640 --> 01:38:40,800
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Brian, get the supplies.

1075
01:39:38,300 --> 01:39:39,926
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, shit. Let's go!

1076
01:39:40,769 --> 01:39:41,826
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Pull, Brian!

1077
01:40:18,072 --> 01:40:20,164
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Take the medicine to Laura.

1078
01:40:51,672 --> 01:40:54,606
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We're almost there. Come on!

1079
01:40:55,709 --> 01:40:58,575
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Brian! Close the door!

1080
01:41:09,757 --> 01:41:12,088
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Don't let the fire go out!

1081
01:41:12,259 --> 01:41:13,987
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What's happening?

1082
01:41:21,735 --> 01:41:23,429
{\fncambria\fs22\shad2\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Buddha, come away from the door.

